# Approach 3: Partition Method (Optimal)

This is similar to **QuickSort partitioning**.

### Idea

Maintain a pointer `pos` that indicates where the **next 0 should go**.

When a `0` is found:

* swap it with `arr[pos]`
* increment `pos`

### Code

```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    void segregate0and1(vector<int> &arr) {

        int pos = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < arr.size(); i++) {

            if(arr[i] == 0) {
                swap(arr[i], arr[pos]);
                pos++;
            }
        }
    }
};
```

### Complexity

| Metric | Value |
| ------ | ----- |
| Time   | O(n)  |
| Space  | O(1)  |

